# Git Workflow

- Keep commits focused on one logical change; avoid mixing unrelated edits.
- Use conventional prefixes: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `chore`, `docs`, `test`.
- Write commit titles as one concise line in imperative mood.
- Include a short body when context is needed: why the change exists and impact.
- Run relevant checks before commit (`lint`, `test`, or targeted validation).
- Do not rewrite shared history unless explicitly requested.
